	   <tr><td colspan=2>Picking the right weapon is a very challenging thing to do.&nbsp;&nbsp;As an SK, you probably will be casting spells in battle, so one could argue that a 2H weapon benefits an SK the most (assuming you time the casts correctly), becuase you can cast in between swings (2H weapons generally take longer to swing than 1H weapons).  Further, you will hit harder due to the dmg bonus that you will receive (not considering caps---longer delay = more dmg bonus on 2H weapon).  A 1H weapon, however, benefits you in that you can wield a shield, which increases your AC &amp; allows you to bash (interrupt spell casting, which can be very important--wait until you goto PoG and the MOB gates, heals up, then starts summoning all the peeps in your raid for a little 1-on-1 attention--all becuase he wasnt stunned).  Further, you can bash for additional dmg--not a lot, but every bit helps.  With that in mind--hell--take yor pick.<br><br>At lower levels, a 1H weapon might benefit you the most due to dmg cap.  Personally, if I was going to pick the 3 main skills that I would be practicing, they would be 1HB, 1HS &amp; 2HS.  Pierce &amp; 2HB can be nice, but the aforementioned are just MADE for an SK.  For instance, the top 5 dmg per sec 1HB weapons are all SK only or SK/PLD only.  1HS follows a similar theme.  The reason for this might be that PLDs &amp; SKs cant duel wield, so Verant makes up for it by giving them better weapons than the WAR/RGR can wield, but who really knows...<br><br>2HS is also nice because 1) the SK epic is 2HS &amp; 2) due to maximizing your spell casting ability (see above).  Further, it isnt uncommon to be in a grp where the objective is to just do as much dmg as possible--kill the MOB as quickly as possible.  Often times, that will be accomplished with a 2H weapon--not a 1H weapon.  I know what you are thinking--Isn't that what you always want to do?  Well, I think so.  But ask a WAR why they are wielding a Jade Mace &amp; not a Wurm--Wurm has better buffs, as well as a better dmg per sec.  They will cite TAUNT as their primary objective.  To be honest, Im not real sure that the number of times hit has a greater taunt effect than dmg anyways, but the WAR have their own mentality, so....<br><br>As far as actual weapon choices, I just LOVE a Blackened Alloy Bastard Sword--dmg per sec will actually be higher than a wurm (although Wurm is 1HS--which is DEFINITELY better).  These are really cheap on my server (Xev)--probably 200-300pp or so.  Further, if you can spend a 1k, a MoSS is definitely what you want, til you can upgrade to an Ebon Mace.<br><br>If you want to stick with 1HS, than a Wurm is what you really want.  That might be a little expensive though (1.5K on my server).  a Sarnak Skullsplitter isnt too bad, but not worth it for the $$$ to me, but cheaper than a Wurm.<br><br>Hope that helps<br><br>Lunaticfringe<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
